  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\n Geth/v1.9.21-stable-0287d548/windows-amd64/go1.15\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI open geth console and run the following command \r\n\r\n```\r\n> eth.blockNumber\r\n329\r\n> admin.sleepBlocks(1)\r\ntrue\r\n> eth.blockNumber\r\n```\r\n\r\nSince I run this on a private chain, I expect admin.sleepBlocks to block the console until I have mined 1 block. Further,  I expect eth.blockNumber to be 330 because admin.sleepBlocks waits 1 block then return.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nadmin.sleepBlocks(1) returns immediately on my private chain without any miner working. \r\n\r\nFurther, eth.blockNumber is still 329.\r\n\r\n",
